<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="417" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1302,1687]" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,294,1302,1327]" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[300,359,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Adult</emphasis>
: Wing (
<figureCitation box="[448,513,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1937,1959]" captionTargetBox="[234,1333,196,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[229,1344,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 14. Helianthecis capitum. 7, Head (frontal, flagella removed). 8, Male third flagellomere (ventral). 9, Female third flagellomere (ventral). 10, Acropod (lateral). 11, Male terminalia (lateral). 12, Same, one gonopod removed (dorsal). 13, Same (ventral). 14, Male sixth (on left) through eighth abdominal tergites." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263702/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) length: male 5.6–6.0 (n=7, avg.=5.7); female 
<quantity box="[1026,1158,1302,1327]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="5.3" metricValueMin="4.7" pageId="14" pageNumber="417" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="5.3" valueMin="4.7">4.7–5.3 mm</quantity>
(n=6, avg.=5.1). Head as in 
<figureCitation box="[182,266,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 39" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,415,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[150,1436,396,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 39. Chiosperma turgidum. 33, Head (frontal, flagella removed). 34, Male third flagellomere (ventral). 35, Female third flagellomere (ventral). 36, Claw and empodium (lateral). 37, Acropod (mesal). 38, Pupal anterior parts (ventral, part of an antennal base missing). 39, End of ovipositor (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263707/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
, palpus 1- or 2-segmented, antennal flagellomeres as in 
<figureCitation box="[912,1042,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 39" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,415,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[150,1436,396,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 39. Chiosperma turgidum. 33, Head (frontal, flagella removed). 34, Male third flagellomere (ventral). 35, Female third flagellomere (ventral). 36, Claw and empodium (lateral). 37, Acropod (mesal). 38, Pupal anterior parts (ventral, part of an antennal base missing). 39, End of ovipositor (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263707/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Figs 34–35</figureCitation>
. Acropods as in 
<figureCitation box="[1237,1366,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 39" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,415,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[150,1436,396,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 39. Chiosperma turgidum. 33, Head (frontal, flagella removed). 34, Male third flagellomere (ventral). 35, Female third flagellomere (ventral). 36, Claw and empodium (lateral). 37, Acropod (mesal). 38, Pupal anterior parts (ventral, part of an antennal base missing). 39, End of ovipositor (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263707/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Figs 36–37</figureCitation>
. Male terminalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[327,408,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 41" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[317,1274,205,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[286,1282,193,1925]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 41. Chiosperma turgidum. 40, Male terminalia, one gonopod removed, one mediobasal gonocoxal lobe visible between lobes of hypoproct (dorsal), aedeagus not shown. 41, Male terminalia (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263708/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Figs 41</figureCitation>
–42. Female postabdomen as in 
<figureCitation box="[763,846,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 32" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[159,1426,340,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[150,1436,340,1891]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 32. Female abdomens, end of fourth segment to cerci (dorsolateral). 31, Lonicerae russoi. 32, Chiosperma turgidum. Letter a: position of lateral setae on fifth tergite, at midlength on L. russoi, farther anteriad on C. turgidum; b: presence of scales on L. russoi, their absence on C. turgidum; c: weakly sclerotized area of seventh sternite anteriad of the posterior setal rows; d: lateral sclerite of protrusible part of the ovipositor. Line = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263706/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Figs 32</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[858,889,1375,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 39" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,415,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[150,1436,396,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 39. Chiosperma turgidum. 33, Head (frontal, flagella removed). 34, Male third flagellomere (ventral). 35, Female third flagellomere (ventral). 36, Claw and empodium (lateral). 37, Acropod (mesal). 38, Pupal anterior parts (ventral, part of an antennal base missing). 39, End of ovipositor (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263707/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">39</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1302,1687]" box="[199,912,1410,1435]" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">
<emphasis box="[199,258,1411,1434]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Pupa</emphasis>
