<figureCitation box="[493,575,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 39" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,415,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[150,1436,396,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 39. Chiosperma turgidum. 33, Head (frontal, flagella removed). 34, Male third flagellomere (ventral). 35, Female third flagellomere (ventral). 36, Claw and empodium (lateral). 37, Acropod (mesal). 38, Pupal anterior parts (ventral, part of an antennal base missing). 39, End of ovipositor (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263707/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
) as in the generic description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1302,1687]" box="[199,1121,1446,1471]" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">
<emphasis box="[199,266,1447,1470]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Larva</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[280,404,1446,1470]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">third instar</emphasis>
