<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="417" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1302,1687]" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1554,1579]" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name 
<taxonomicName box="[552,652,1555,1579]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Chiosperma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dipsacales" pageId="14" pageNumber="417" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="turgidum">
<emphasis box="[552,652,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">turgidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Latin for swollen) refers to the enlargement of host's buds caused by this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1302,1687]" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1626,1651]" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Life history</emphasis>
. This species is responsible for an elongate, swollen bud gall (
<figureCitation box="[1051,1118,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1554,1576]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,519,1523]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[150,1436,519,1532]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Galls. 1, Lonicerae russoi on Lonicera hispidula (photo by R. Russo). 2, Lonicerae lonicera on Lonicera subspicata (photo by R. Russo). 3, Chiosperma turgidum on Symphoricarpos albus (photo by M. Althaus). Line = actual size of gall." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263700/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) on 
<taxonomicName box="[1172,1428,1627,1651]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Symphorocarpos" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dipsacales" pageId="14" pageNumber="417" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albus">
<emphasis box="[1172,1428,1627,1651]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="417">Symphorocarpos albus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Buds are enlarged, about 
<quantity box="[436,501,1662,1687]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="417" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
wide by 
<quantity box="[604,711,1663,1687]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="417" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8–10 mm</quantity>
long, and do not open.
</paragraph>
